sections.heading: Overview
content: Dr. Lily Jung, MD, is a practicing neurologist in the state of Washington.

Jung graduated from Northwestern University Medical School, then completed her residency at University of Washington Medical School.  Jung has a masters in medical management from the Tulane University of Public Health and Tropical Medicine.

She is a clinical assistant professor in neurology at University of Washington Medical School.  She is also a member of the American College of Physician Executives as well as the American Academy of Neurology.
Jung is board certified by the American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology, with a subspecialty certificate in neurology.
She is a physician reviewer for Physicians’ Review Network, Inc., an independent medical review organization.
